The Mah<193>bh<193>rata, also known as the Pa<210>cama Veda (`the ç
fifth Veda'), is a veritable encyclopaedia of Hindu religion and culture. ç
The claim of the S<220>ta Ugra·ravas that `anything anywhere is an ç
echo of what is here' and `what is not here is nowhere' is no exaggeration. ç
