<193>pad-dharma (conduct permissible during dire calamities), d<193>na-dharma ç
(liberality) or mok<218>a-dharma (conduct pertaining to emancipation)†finds ç
its due place here. In fact, the very purpose of the Mah<193>bh<193>rata ç
is to expound dharma in all its ramifications. The celebrated Bhagavadg<200>t<193>, ç
the less known Anug<200>t<193>, as also the two well-known hymns ç
Vi<218><207>u- sahasran<193>ma and <185>ivasahasran<193>ma, have ç
been sources of inspiration to philosophers and votaries of religious ç
pursuits over the millennia. The cult of Vi<218><207>u and the reconciliation ç
of the various warring faiths also find an appropriate place. Along ç
with the growth of rigidity of the caste system, honest attempts at ç
extolling human excellence and treating it as the real basis of br<193>hma<207>ahood ç
are also conspicuous. In spite of the misogynists of the age, women ç
did find a place of honour during the epic period.
